{
  "texts": [
    "The educational sector is now beginning to recognise the potential benefits of GenAI, albeit reluctantly, leading to a more nuanced approach to its integration.",
    "This acceptance reflects a broader recognition that the use of technology in the workplace and in academic settings may have the ability to enhance performance and learning experiences.",
    "(Black & Lynch, 2001; Higgins et al., 2012; Oldham & Da Silva, 2015; Schacter, 1999).",
    "This change is part of a larger narrative where new technologies, initially met with scepticism and labelled as threats to genuine learning, gradually find their place as indispensable elements in education.",
    "Calculators, word processors, and the Internet have each shared their turn as 'the end of students doing real learning' only to become standard practice within a few years of general availability."
  ]
}